Carl Stefan Erling Persson (; born 4 October 1947) is a Swedish businessman.
In March 2013, Forbes reported Persson's net worth as $28 billion. making him the richest of Sweden's 12 billionaires and the 17th richest person in the world;
Persson is the chairman and main shareholder in fashion company H&M, which was founded by his father Erling Persson in 1947.
